# Configuration

- Test configuration: `appsettings.LowLimitsTest.json` (low thresholds for quick alert generation)
- Production configuration: `appsettings.json`
- TestTimeoutSeconds should be 30 for testing
- Always verify config is copied correctly before testing

## MANDATORY: UNC Config Files Are the Production Standard

The **UNC network share is the single source of truth** for all ServerMonitorAgent configuration files. The local files are cached copies that are **automatically overwritten** by pre-build scripts during every `dotnet build` / `dotnet publish`.

This applies to **both** of these files:

| UNC file (production standard) | Local file (cached copy) |
|---|---|
| `C:\opt\src\DedgeSrc\DedgeSystemTools\Folders\DedgeCommon\Software\Config\ServerMonitor\appsettings.ServerMonitorAgent.json` | `C:\opt\src\ServerMonitor\ServerMonitorAgent\src\ServerMonitor\appsettings.json` |
| `C:\opt\src\DedgeSrc\DedgeSystemTools\Folders\DedgeCommon\Software\Config\ServerMonitor\NotificationRecipients.json` | `C:\opt\src\ServerMonitor\ServerMonitorAgent\src\ServerMonitor\NotificationRecipients.json` |

### Why

Pre-build scripts copy FROM the UNC share TO local on every build. Any local-only changes **will be destroyed** on the next build.

### Mandatory Workflow — For Now and All Future

**When making ANY change to either config file:**

1. **Copy the UNC file TO local first** — ensures you start from the current production version
2. **Edit the local file** using editor tools (Grep/StrReplace cannot access UNC paths directly)
3. **Copy the local file back TO the UNC share** — this makes the UNC share the new production standard
4. **Also copy to the published agent folder** if a build has already published (so the running agent picks up the change)

#### appsettings.json

```powershell
# Step 1: Pull current production config from UNC to local
Copy-Item -Path "C:\opt\src\DedgeSrc\DedgeSystemTools\Folders\DedgeCommon\Software\Config\ServerMonitor\appsettings.ServerMonitorAgent.json" `
  -Destination "C:\opt\src\ServerMonitor\ServerMonitorAgent\src\ServerMonitor\appsettings.json" -Force

# Step 2: (Edit the local file using StrReplace / Read tools)

# Step 3: Push local changes back to UNC share (production standard)
Copy-Item -Path "C:\opt\src\ServerMonitor\ServerMonitorAgent\src\ServerMonitor\appsettings.json" `
  -Destination "C:\opt\src\DedgeSrc\DedgeSystemTools\Folders\DedgeCommon\Software\Config\ServerMonitor\appsettings.ServerMonitorAgent.json" -Force

# Step 4: Push to published agent folder (so running agents get the update)
Copy-Item -Path "C:\opt\src\ServerMonitor\ServerMonitorAgent\src\ServerMonitor\appsettings.json" `
  -Destination "C:\opt\src\DedgeSrc\DedgeSystemTools\Folders\DedgeCommon\Software\DedgeWinApps\ServerMonitor\appsettings.json" -Force
```

#### NotificationRecipients.json

```powershell
# Step 1: Pull current production config from UNC to local
Copy-Item -Path "C:\opt\src\DedgeSrc\DedgeSystemTools\Folders\DedgeCommon\Software\Config\ServerMonitor\NotificationRecipients.json" `
  -Destination "C:\opt\src\ServerMonitor\ServerMonitorAgent\src\ServerMonitor\NotificationRecipients.json" -Force

# Step 2: (Edit the local file using StrReplace / Read tools)

# Step 3: Push local changes back to UNC share (production standard)
Copy-Item -Path "C:\opt\src\ServerMonitor\ServerMonitorAgent\src\ServerMonitor\NotificationRecipients.json" `
  -Destination "C:\opt\src\DedgeSrc\DedgeSystemTools\Folders\DedgeCommon\Software\Config\ServerMonitor\NotificationRecipients.json" -Force

# Step 4: Push to published agent folder (so running agents get the update)
Copy-Item -Path "C:\opt\src\ServerMonitor\ServerMonitorAgent\src\ServerMonitor\NotificationRecipients.json" `
  -Destination "C:\opt\src\DedgeSrc\DedgeSystemTools\Folders\DedgeCommon\Software\DedgeWinApps\ServerMonitor\NotificationRecipients.json" -Force
```

**NEVER skip steps 1 or 3.** Step 1 ensures you don't lose production changes. Step 3 ensures your edits become the new standard. If you build without step 3, your changes will be destroyed.

### Verification After Changes

After modifying and copying, always verify the UNC file has the expected content:

```powershell
Select-String -Path "C:\opt\src\DedgeSrc\DedgeSystemTools\Folders\DedgeCommon\Software\Config\ServerMonitor\appsettings.ServerMonitorAgent.json" -Pattern "<key phrase from your change>"
Select-String -Path "C:\opt\src\DedgeSrc\DedgeSystemTools\Folders\DedgeCommon\Software\Config\ServerMonitor\NotificationRecipients.json" -Pattern "<key phrase from your change>"
```

### During Build-And-Publish

The `Build-And-Publish.ps1` script triggers the pre-build sync. If you have pending local changes that haven't been pushed to UNC yet, they **will be overwritten**. Always push to UNC before building.
